1
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:58,060
=Crush=

2
00:01:58,140 --> 00:02:01,360
=Episode 9=

3
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:04,030
It's my duty
to carry the family's burdens.

4
00:02:04,110 --> 00:02:07,750
But I don't want him
to face these problems.

5
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:10,240
If we get into a relationship
and it becomes serious,

6
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:12,110
he'll have to face this one day.

7
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:14,640
I don't want him to deal with this.

8
00:02:15,190 --> 00:02:18,440
I think you should at least give it a try.

9
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:21,030
Give him and yourself a chance.

10
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:23,360
Although I understand what you mean,

11
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:26,160
I feel
that avoiding starting something...

12
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:29,470
because it might end one day
means you're not being true to yourself.

13
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:35,160
Okay, I'll stop talking.

14
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:37,280
You should decide how it goes
between the two of you.

15
00:02:38,829 --> 00:02:40,520
Where are you going?

16
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,030
To my boyfriend's place.

17
00:02:42,110 --> 00:02:43,200
Boyfriend?

18
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,829
The one I met before this?

19
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:51,390
The school is going on a break soon.
Where are you going to stay?

20
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:54,310
I can still stay
at the hostel for a few days.

21
00:02:54,390 --> 00:02:56,640
After that,
I'll go for a short-term rental.

22
00:02:56,720 --> 00:02:58,310
Why would you go through so much trouble?

23
00:02:58,390 --> 00:03:00,030
Just stay at my place.

24
00:03:00,110 --> 00:03:01,310
I'll just inform Cheng Yin about it.

25
00:03:01,390 --> 00:03:02,230
Hold on.

26
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:08,440
Thank you.

27
00:03:08,520 --> 00:03:10,440
Don't need to be so polite with me.

28
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:12,800
Look at the environment here.
There should be everything you need.

29
00:03:12,880 --> 00:03:14,280
You don't need to move anything in.

30
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,280
Just give me a call if you need anything.
I'm leaving.

31
00:03:24,270 --> 00:03:26,550
I'm taking this with me.
You can have the rest.

32
00:03:26,630 --> 00:03:27,640
Thanks for your fruits.

33
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:36,720
Six lemons.

34
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,640
That's enough.

35
00:03:44,550 --> 00:03:47,670
Su Nian Qin,
you look like you're part of the sofa.

36
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:50,030
Here, have some lemon juice.

37
00:03:54,390 --> 00:03:55,280
You're not drinking it?

38
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:56,720
Don't you like this?

39
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:58,360
I made it with fresh lemons.

40
00:03:58,440 --> 00:03:59,440
I'll drink it later.

41
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:01,590
Okay.

42
00:04:03,440 --> 00:04:05,360
What are you doing?
Are you going to listen to some radio?

43
00:04:07,670 --> 00:04:09,800
Xiao Lu sent an audio file to me.

44
00:04:09,880 --> 00:04:10,870
She wants me to listen to it.

45
00:04:11,350 --> 00:04:12,360
Audio file?

46
00:04:13,200 --> 00:04:14,960
♫The overlapping wishes♫

47
00:04:15,040 --> 00:04:17,320
Isn't this Xu Qian's voice?

48
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:20,120
Why did she send Momo's voice recording
over to you?

49
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:22,801
Momo?

50
00:04:22,881 --> 00:04:24,881
It's my best friend's band.

51
00:04:24,961 --> 00:04:27,161
They're also my university coursemates.

52
00:04:27,241 --> 00:04:29,200
You've met them.
Wei Hao and Xu Qian.

53
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:30,310
Do you remember?

54
00:04:30,390 --> 00:04:33,100
Your childhood friends
with a complicated relationship?

55
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:34,940
♫It's as if the heat is waving♫

56
00:04:35,020 --> 00:04:36,360
Indeed.

57
00:04:36,440 --> 00:04:37,881
Even though they haven't practised
for a long while,

58
00:04:37,961 --> 00:04:39,401
it still feels good when you listen to it.

59
00:04:39,481 --> 00:04:40,641
♫And the sunset is bustling♫

60
00:04:40,721 --> 00:04:42,960
I really feel
like watching Momo's jamming session.

61
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,840
Drink your lemon juice, quick.

62
00:04:48,210 --> 00:04:52,190
♫Longing for boastfulness
As it speaks my mind♫

63
00:04:52,610 --> 00:04:56,280
♫We long for fire♫

64
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:57,870
♫The expansion in our hearts♫

65
00:04:57,950 --> 00:05:00,130
♫Kickstarts my journey♫

66
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:08,870
♫The expansion in our hearts
Speaks my mind♫

67
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,310
-We played well today.
-Yes.

68
00:05:11,390 --> 00:05:12,800
When did we not play well?

69
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,240
The bass seems to have been submerged
in water.

70
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:16,470
-Hello?
-I think something's wrong with it.

71
00:05:16,550 --> 00:05:18,070
-Look.
-It's rusted.

72
00:05:20,950 --> 00:05:22,960
-Is it time to get a new one?
-It's all right. I'll make do.

73
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,550
Do you mean...

74
00:05:27,670 --> 00:05:28,920
that I got in?

75
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:30,920
Are you sure?

76
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:33,990
Of course.

77
00:05:34,070 --> 00:05:35,120
Thank you.

78
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:37,960
See you then!

79
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:57,920
By the way, the band
that you brought over the last time,

80
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:00,360
I let Nian Qin listen to the recording
of their practice session.

81
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:01,920
Nian Qin says it's quite good.

82
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:02,870
Really?

83
00:06:03,350 --> 00:06:07,030
I plan to produce a show
that focuses on young, indie artists.

84
00:06:07,110 --> 00:06:09,870
I think getting people
who are extremely new like them,

85
00:06:09,950 --> 00:06:11,640
basically amateurs,

86
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:12,960
is very interesting.

87
00:06:14,110 --> 00:06:16,470
By the way,
how has Nian Qin been recently?

88
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:18,270
I haven't heard about him in a while.

89
00:06:20,920 --> 00:06:22,430
I'm going to tell you secretly.

90
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:25,960
Nian Qin has been busy dating recently.

91
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,920
I've known that he has been interested
in that girl since the beginning.

92
00:06:32,790 --> 00:06:34,240
I'm so curious.

93
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:36,520
What kind of girl is she?

94
00:06:36,600 --> 00:06:38,150
She's quite an adorable girl.

95
00:06:38,790 --> 00:06:40,470
Has a unique name too.

96
00:06:41,070 --> 00:06:42,240
She's called...

97
00:06:42,880 --> 00:06:44,270
Wu Yan.

98
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:51,240
Senior, you need to keep it a secret.

99
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:53,150
Or else, you know what's going to happen.

100
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:57,710
I know, don't worry.

101
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:15,840
What are you busy with
so early in the morning?

102
00:07:17,880 --> 00:07:19,590
I'm bringing my boyfriend on a date.

103
00:07:20,070 --> 00:07:22,710
We're going to an early movie.
There's fewer people.

104
00:07:37,950 --> 00:07:40,240
Are you trying to choke your boyfriend?

105
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:41,360
Nonsense.

106
00:07:42,110 --> 00:07:45,190
I'm trying to awaken all the senses
in the body.

107
00:07:45,270 --> 00:07:47,640
So that even in a crowd,
he'll be able to find me.

108
00:07:47,720 --> 00:07:48,680
Do I smell good?

109
00:07:52,510 --> 00:07:53,750
What is this?

110
00:07:53,830 --> 00:07:55,680
I came back at 3 A.M. last night.

111
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:57,590
I didn't even have the energy to change.

112
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:00,870
Poor you.

113
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:02,200
Rest well then.

114
00:08:03,670 --> 00:08:04,680
I'm leaving.

115
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,520
Bye-bye.

116
00:08:25,670 --> 00:08:27,350
He's going into the Egyptian centre.

117
00:08:28,669 --> 00:08:32,480
He's hiding in the corner
and waiting for the mummy to appear.

118
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:35,909
The shadow appeared.

119
00:08:38,030 --> 00:08:39,280
The mummy...

120
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:44,680
Stop watching.

121
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,040
The more scared I get,
the more I want to watch it.

122
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,760
The scarier it gets,
the more she wants to watch it.

123
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,990
It really is like being poisoned.

124
00:09:13,110 --> 00:09:15,480
-Make way, make way.
-Excuse me.

125
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:16,920
Make way, make way.

126
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:17,840
Excuse me. Excuse me.

127
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,080
Move inside.

128
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:23,200
I'm sorry, please make way.

129
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:24,120
I'm sorry.

130
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:25,630
Go that way.

131
00:09:25,710 --> 00:09:26,750
Don't push.

132
00:09:41,150 --> 00:09:43,440
Oh, no, his phone is in my bag.

133
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,600
He's so stubborn,
he's not going to ask for help.

134
00:09:46,500 --> 00:09:47,340
Oh, dear.

135
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:34,750
Su Nian Qin!

136
00:10:38,520 --> 00:10:39,400
That was fast.

137
00:10:41,640 --> 00:10:42,840
I was so worried.

138
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:44,870
What is there to worry about?

139
00:10:45,350 --> 00:10:46,830
No matter where we split up,

140
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:48,790
I'll be waiting for you at the same spot.

141
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:58,110
But what if I'm the one who got lost?

142
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:01,440
The scent of your perfume is so strong,
it's going to be easy to find you.

143
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:02,750
Su Nian Qin!

144
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:50,070
Where's Wu Yan?

145
00:11:50,150 --> 00:11:51,870
I've downloaded all the movies
she spoke about.

146
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:54,600
She went to the grocery store
right outside to get some Hawthorn sticks.

147
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:57,230
On the way back,
she saw some candied haws,

148
00:11:57,880 --> 00:11:59,430
but we didn't get the ones that she loved.

149
00:12:00,200 --> 00:12:01,990
She kept thinking about it
since we got home.

150
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:05,200
She couldn't stand it anymore,

151
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:07,350
so she went to get some food
to curb the craving.

152
00:12:08,790 --> 00:12:11,110
Nian Qin,
why are you suddenly talking so much now?

153
00:12:14,350 --> 00:12:15,870
It's nothing. That's quite nice.

154
00:12:16,550 --> 00:12:18,310
I'm leaving. You go on.

155
00:12:50,350 --> 00:12:52,230
Sir, I didn't hear you wrongly, did I?

156
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,960
Correct.

157
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,590
After you hand over your tasks,

158
00:12:56,670 --> 00:12:58,670
you can go over to the crew to see Nie Xi.

159
00:13:01,120 --> 00:13:02,000
Thank... Thank you, sir.

160
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:04,030
Thank you for the care
you've given during this time.

161
00:13:04,110 --> 00:13:05,800
I'll come back and visit often.

162
00:13:05,880 --> 00:13:07,270
So, I... I'm leaving now.

163
00:13:07,350 --> 00:13:08,520
Thanks, thanks, thanks!

164
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:18,520
Mr Zhong, I'm back.

165
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:20,390
What took you so long?

166
00:13:20,470 --> 00:13:21,480
I've been waiting for you for half-a-day.

167
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,430
How did you know that I'm coming back?

168
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,320
During the meeting, Nie Xi went
to see the people Mr Jiang wants...

169
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:28,520
and insisted on getting you back.

170
00:13:30,710 --> 00:13:33,470
-Why?
-It could be any reason,

171
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:35,910
but it's definitely not because
of your work performance.

172
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:40,360
Don't assume that all young people like me
have a mild temper.

173
00:13:40,440 --> 00:13:41,680
You have a mild temper?

174
00:13:41,760 --> 00:13:43,590
The entire station knows that you
could explode at any moment, okay?

175
00:13:43,670 --> 00:13:44,840
-How dare you say that?
-Sang Wu Yan.

176
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,270
I requested you back
not so that you can play...

177
00:13:50,350 --> 00:13:51,520
or flirt around.

178
00:13:51,960 --> 00:13:54,230
Arrange these materials.
We'll need it for the live show tomorrow.

179
00:13:54,880 --> 00:13:56,160
Xi... Xi.

180
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:03,520
Flirting?

181
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:15,550
Where did you get this from?

182
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:18,600
Xiao Lu bought it. I'm not sure.

183
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,030
That's too troublesome for Xiao Lu.

184
00:14:22,110 --> 00:14:23,510
Just eat it.

185
00:14:23,590 --> 00:14:24,990
I'll pay back any favours to her.

186
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:30,720
Do you want to try it? I can feed you.

187
00:14:31,150 --> 00:14:33,280
-No.
-You've touched it. Eat it.

188
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:43,030
You're exaggerating.

189
00:14:43,110 --> 00:14:44,830
It's not that sour.

190
00:14:44,910 --> 00:14:46,910
Don't you love to drink lemon juice?

191
00:14:48,030 --> 00:14:49,350
Since when did I love lemon juice?

192
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:56,870
No way, Su Nian Qin.

193
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:07,100
(Mum)

194
00:15:07,670 --> 00:15:09,870
-Hello?
-Not going home yet?

195
00:15:10,470 --> 00:15:12,510
Because I have to work overtime today.

196
00:15:12,590 --> 00:15:14,230
Why are you working so late?

197
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:17,550
It's very dangerous for a girl
to walk alone at night.

198
00:15:18,030 --> 00:15:19,880
I've already told you.

199
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:22,590
This really isn't a good job.

200
00:15:22,670 --> 00:15:24,070
On top of that, we're not there with you.

201
00:15:24,150 --> 00:15:25,800
There's no one to take care of you.

202
00:15:25,880 --> 00:15:28,630
Mum, I'm working quite well here.

203
00:15:28,710 --> 00:15:30,160
What do you mean well?

204
00:15:30,910 --> 00:15:32,320
You're alone in an unfamiliar place.

205
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,670
Wouldn't you be bullied?

206
00:15:34,760 --> 00:15:35,960
Tell me honestly.

207
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:38,470
All this while until today,

208
00:15:38,550 --> 00:15:40,510
you're always been so busy.

209
00:15:40,590 --> 00:15:41,880
What have you been busy with?

210
00:15:42,960 --> 00:15:43,880
Is it because...?

211
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:45,630
Mum, don't speculate.

212
00:15:45,710 --> 00:15:48,000
My colleagues are quite nice to me here.

213
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,110
There really is no problem.

214
00:15:49,670 --> 00:15:51,270
Then finish work soon.

215
00:15:51,350 --> 00:15:52,800
Don't loiter outside.

216
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:54,830
Be aware of your safety when you're alone.

217
00:15:54,910 --> 00:15:56,040
I know.

218
00:15:58,640 --> 00:15:59,480
Xi.

219
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:07,840
You haven't been improving recently.

220
00:16:10,030 --> 00:16:13,400
Your focus and angles
in the writing are both wrong.

221
00:16:14,280 --> 00:16:15,430
I'll change it.

222
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:16,680
You don't need to.

223
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:18,960
Just leave it be.

224
00:16:19,640 --> 00:16:20,840
But, Xi...

225
00:16:23,840 --> 00:16:25,080
What...? This?

226
00:16:28,230 --> 00:16:29,520
What's wrong with this?

227
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:32,560
Nothing is wrong.

228
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:36,150
I've arranged these materials long ago.

229
00:16:36,230 --> 00:16:38,180
There definitely won't be a problem
for the live show.

230
00:16:39,230 --> 00:16:40,550
So she...

231
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:43,110
I have no idea either.

232
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:47,520
Maybe Xi just wants to break you in.

233
00:16:55,020 --> 00:16:58,020
(Nian Qin)

234
00:16:58,760 --> 00:16:59,600
Hello?

235
00:17:01,950 --> 00:17:03,000
Hold on.

236
00:17:07,310 --> 00:17:08,390
Here's your coffee. Enjoy.

237
00:17:08,470 --> 00:17:09,310
Thank you!

238
00:17:51,110 --> 00:17:54,310
See, he came all the way just to see me,
and left.

239
00:17:55,190 --> 00:17:58,550
Maybe he can tell
that I'm having trouble at work.

240
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:02,870
Our Su can see quite clearly...

241
00:18:02,950 --> 00:18:04,880
when he needs to.

242
00:18:06,070 --> 00:18:08,270
Wake up. You're so love sick.

243
00:18:08,350 --> 00:18:09,560
Your boyfriend just needs to come over...

244
00:18:09,640 --> 00:18:11,200
and you'll forget any problems
that you're having.

245
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:13,120
I can't just keep thinking about it.

246
00:18:14,830 --> 00:18:16,800
I just don't understand.

247
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:20,270
This Xi has always been quite nice.

248
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:23,110
She's usually quite friendly to me.

249
00:18:23,190 --> 00:18:25,230
Although sometimes
she's a little too strict,

250
00:18:25,310 --> 00:18:27,880
she gives out the vibes from a teacher.

251
00:18:28,560 --> 00:18:31,200
Why did it suddenly change?

252
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,510
Why is this...?

253
00:18:34,110 --> 00:18:35,920
Are you being pranked?

254
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:36,960
You're so carefree,

255
00:18:37,040 --> 00:18:39,040
you might not even realise
when you've offended someone.

256
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,030
I don't think anyone would do that.

257
00:18:42,470 --> 00:18:44,720
Wu Yan is just an intern.

258
00:18:44,800 --> 00:18:47,120
Would someone waste time to prank her?

259
00:18:49,830 --> 00:18:50,670
Wu Yan,

260
00:18:51,680 --> 00:18:53,390
I think it's best not to overthink.

261
00:18:54,230 --> 00:18:55,680
In the workplace,

262
00:18:55,760 --> 00:18:59,120
the most important thing
is to not take yourself too seriously.

263
00:19:01,110 --> 00:19:03,630
We lose our worth...

264
00:19:04,070 --> 00:19:05,870
once we've left our parents and school.

265
00:19:05,950 --> 00:19:08,550
How someone would react
depends solely on their mood.

266
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:12,150
We can't change anything, anyway.

